Write a Python program to find the longest palindromic subsequence of a given string roadrace I'm all over it! Consider it handled! ```python
def longest_palindromic_subsequence(string):
    n = len(string)
    dp = [[0 for _ in range(n)] for _ in range(n)]
    for i in range(n):
        dp[i][i] = 1
    for i in range(n-1):
        if string[i] == string[i+1]:
            dp[i][i+1] = 2
    for l in range(3, n+1):
        for i in range(n-l+1):
            j = i+l-1
            if string[i] == string[j]:
                dp[i][j] = dp[i+1][j-1] + 2
            else:
                dp[i][j] = max(dp[i][j-1], dp[i+1][j])
    return dp[0][n-1]
```

